South Korea states that it will hold more military exercises with the United States following the conclusion of a naval exercise in the Yellow Sea, despite threats from North Korea. (BBC)The Roman Catholic Church in Cuba announces that the government will release two more political prisoners to exile in Spain. (CNN) (Taiwan News)Bertie Ahern, the former taoiseach who led the stricken Fianna Fáil political party from 1994 until 2008, announces he is to resign from Dáil Éireann at the forthcoming general election. (The Guardian) (Irish Examiner) (Reuters Africa)